window.bookSummaryJSON = "Widely recognized as the master of the historical spy novel, <i>New York Times</i> best-selling author Alan Furst takes listeners back to the early days of World War II for a dramatic novel of intrigue and suspense. <p> Bulgaria, 1934. The local fascists have just murdered the brother of Khristo Stoianev. Now Khristo is recruited into the NKVD, the Soviet secret police, for special service in the Spanish civil war.</p>"; 
